The paper discusses the value of less data within the context of AI, which is a key topic in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also reviews the limited track record of Deep Learning in key areas such as Natural Language Processing, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the regulatory and business significance of being able to learn from few data points, which is relevant to Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Cyber-Physical Systems (cs.CY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, and cs.CR, in that order.
